# 'VPURegMapped' Dialect

VPU NN Register Mapped Dialect
The **VPURegMapped Dialect** defines attributes and types common
    for all supported VPU HW architectures. It is used combined with
    arch specific register map dialects (e.g. VPU37XX)
    to represents NN RunTime IR constructs in terms of the MLIR framework.

[./VPURegMapped/_ops_interfaces.md]

[TOC]

## Operation definition

### `VPURegMapped.DeclareTaskBuffer` (vpux::VPURegMapped::DeclareTaskBufferOp)

Buffer Op representing a discrete location of a task in runtime metadataBuffer


Syntax:

```
operation ::= `VPURegMapped.DeclareTaskBuffer` attr-dict
              $task_type `->` type(results)
```


#### Attributes:

| Attribute | MLIR Type | Description |
| :-------: | :-------: | ----------- |
| `task_type` | vpux::VPURegMapped::TaskTypeAttr | The type of the relevant processing code of the VPU for the task

#### Results:

| Result | Description |
| :----: | ----------- |
| `index` | VPUregMapped Index type
